House Judiciary 1
Amendment No. 1 to HB0354
Farmer
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 326 House Bill No. 354*
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 38-6-132(b), is amended by deleting
the first sentence, which presently reads:
Upon receiving a report of suspected elder financial exploitation, the bureau shall
coordinate with the district attorney general in the appropriate judicial district and, when
appropriate, with other law enforcement agencies and adult protective services for
additional investigation of the reported exploitation.
and substituting instead:
Upon receiving a report of suspected elder financial exploitation, the bureau may
investigate the matter when appropriate, and may coordinate with the district attorney
general in the appropriate judicial district, other law enforcement agencies, and adult
protective services for additional investigation of the reported exploitation.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
